            stakeholder maps and the day-by-day cadence we use on engagement.
          </p>
          <ul class="product__list">
            <li>30-day recovery roadmap</li>
            <li>Health-check diagnostic instrument</li>
            <li>Stakeholder &amp; sponsor scripts</li>
            <li>Re-baseline communication kit</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="product__footer">
            <div>
              <div class="product__price">${products.projectRecoveryPack.price}</div>
              <div class="product__price-sub">single user · AUD</div>
            </div>
            <a
              href={recoveryUrl}
              class="lemonsqueezy-button btn btn--primary"
              data-ga-event="product_buy_click"
              data-ga-label="Project Recovery Pack"
              >Buy now <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a
            >
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div
        style="margin-top:3rem; padding:2.5rem; border:1px solid var(--rule); background:var(--paper); display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:2rem; flex-wrap:wrap;"
      >
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
            Free · for delivery leads
          </div>
          <h3
            style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:1.6rem; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:0.5rem;"
          >
            The Project Recovery Checklist
          </h3>
          <p
            style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); max-width:50ch;"
          >
            Twenty-three questions we ask in the first 48 hours of any recovery
            engagement. Print it, take it into your steering meeting, and you'll
            know within an hour where the real problems are.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href="/free-tools/project-recovery-checklist" class="btn btn--primary"
          >Download free <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ENGAGE / FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="engage" data-reveal>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="engage__grid">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Engage Lavelle</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
            Let's talk about <em>what's not moving.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="lead" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
            Whether you need a confidential second opinion on a stalled program,
            a senior delivery lead to take the helm for ninety days, or a PMO
            stood up from scratch — start with a thirty-minute conversation. No
            pitch deck, no obligation, no sales call disguised as a workshop.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__ctas" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">
              Request an engagement conversation <span class="btn__arrow"
                >→</span
              >
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ul class="engage__list" data-reveal data-reveal-stagger>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact?topic=brief"
              ><span>Submit a brief (RFP / EOI)</span><span>→</span></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact?topic=call"
              ><span>Book a 30-minute call with Sky</span><span>→</span></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact?topic=capability"
              ><span>Request a capability statement</span><span>→</span></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact?topic=speaking"
              ><span>Speaking &amp; advisory enquiries</span><span>→</span></a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="/contact?topic=panel"
              ><span>Government panel &amp; supplier listing</span><span>→</span
              ></a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const reveals = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>("[data-reveal]");
  const reduce = window.matchMedia("(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)").matches;

  if (!("IntersectionObserver" in window) || reduce) {
    reveals.forEach((el) => el.classList.add("is-visible"));
  } else {
    const io = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries, obs) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          if (!entry.isIntersecting) continue;
          const el = entry.target as HTMLElement;
          if (el.hasAttribute("data-reveal-stagger")) {
            Array.from(el.children).forEach((child, i) => {
              (child as HTMLElement).style.transitionDelay = `${i * 80}ms`;
            });
          }
          el.classList.add("is-visible");
          obs.unobserve(el);
        }
      },
      { rootMargin: "0px 0px -15% 0px", threshold: 0.1 },
    );
    reveals.forEach((el) => io.observe(el));
  }

  // Banner parallax: image is rendered at its native aspect ratio (taller
  // than the band), so we slide it vertically by up to `slack` pixels as
  // the band scrolls through the viewport. Top edge visible at the start
  // (progress 0), bottom edge visible at the end (progress 1).
  const band = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>(".image-band");
  const bandImg = band?.querySelector<HTMLImageElement>(".image-band__img");
  if (band && bandImg && !reduce) {
    let ticking = false;
    let active = false;

    const update = () => {
      const rect = band.getBoundingClientRect();
      const imgH = bandImg.getBoundingClientRect().height;
      const slack = Math.max(0, imgH - rect.height);
      const vh = window.innerHeight;
      const track = vh + rect.height;
      const consumed = vh - rect.top;
      const progress = Math.max(0, Math.min(1, consumed / track));
      const ty = -progress * slack;
      bandImg.style.transform = `translate3d(0, ${ty}px, 0)`;
      ticking = false;
    };

    const onScroll = () => {
      if (!ticking && active) {
        requestAnimationFrame(update);
        ticking = true;
      }
    };

    const visibility = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        for (const entry of entries) {
          active = entry.isIntersecting;
          if (active) update();
        }
      },
      { rootMargin: "100px 0px 100px 0px" },
    );
    visibility.observe(band);

    window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll, { passive: true });
    window.addEventListener("resize", onScroll, { passive: true });
    if (bandImg.complete) update();
    else bandImg.addEventListener("load", update, { once: true });
  }
</script>
